definitions.definition: The act or practice of stowing.
A place where things are stowed .
examples: Accommodations were so poor I think we were in stowage , with the rest of the cargo.
Our stowage disappeared down the chute, into the employee only cargo area, never to be seen again by man.

definitions.definition: Amount of room for storing things.
A charge for stowing and storage .
examples: We'll have to pay the stowage if we want our crate back.
